<br>
Well at pre-50 I can agree that casters are fairly powerful and gear really isnt all that important compared to melee classes. However post-50 things change and the degree at which mob power grows takes a giant leap forward. Due to mudflation melee are able to deal with the increase in NPC power, but casters cannot due to spell level restrictions. <br>
<br>
Now there are very few buyable spells post 50 and as we all know the really good ones can cost alot.  What does loot mean? When I hear the word &quot;loot&quot; I think anything that drops off of NPCs. If this is the correct definition of loot then casters are very loot dependant post 50 maybe even more so then melee classes and should scale in the same way.<br>
<br>
RBG is something that drops randomly off of Krup frogs in Sebillis. Same goes for many other melee weapons and armor that drops in sebillis. Why is it I have to kill Jugs to get spells to increase in power but a 28% haste item drops in areas of the zone that are no where near the difficulty of Jugs? Why is it I have seen more RBGs drop then I have seen Turpor (always miss spell that damn spell) scrolls? Same goes for Muzzle.  I am very loot dependant. Without spells my power is very limited and by having those spells drop as loot makes me just as in need of loot and items as the melee class fighting next to me. <br>
<br>
Do we want the same things? No, I could care less about a primal 2hs but I want a spell that is on par with primal weapons dropping also.  People like to down play mana/hp/ac items but they make a dramatic difference. What can a lvl60 mage kill with no items that is worth mentioning?  Having extra hp/ac items on has saved me many times. Just like having Jboots and Burntwood stave have saved me a number of times. This idea that casters dont need loot as much as melee is just crap. Maybe that was true pre-50 but things are very different post 50. Mobs are so overpowered compared to PCs that a naked caster is just as helpless as a naked melee. I would venture to say that being able to hide/sneak, FD, use defensive disc, cast spells more then help the naked melee. I have seen many naked warriors use there disc that acts like a 8sec divine aura to make it to the zone. Something aggros the monk he just FD same for the SK.  Hybrids have defensive spells that are on par with casters yet can wield primal and benefit from loot just as pure melee. Paladins have LoH and root even naked. So casters have no advantage naked that puts them anyway over and beyond what melee can do naked. Because of this casters should scale in the same way that melee classes do.  At lvl56 I have dropped near 30k for spells to increase my power. These spells didnt cost 28p off of a vendor. So I wish people would stop talking about vendor purchased spells. Most of the good spells post 50 are dropped and most drop in no so pleasant areas of zones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucolleen2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Colleen2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/02 7:05:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=ht