<br>
Whereas I am not overly against twinking, I mean I hate letting all those loots rot in the bank, it does serve as a barrier to entry for new players, who cannot compete with twinks and will only become frustrated.  Making it so that all classes are subject to twinking will make it difficult to recruit and retain new players, but will only serve the interest of existing players with excess loot.<br>
<br>
The fact that casters are less gear dependent allows for character-centered players as opposed to loot-centered players.  The current situation with spells being character-centered versus gear being loot-centered enables a spectrum of gear dependency.  That is pure casters are the most independent of gear, followed by priests, hybrids can overcome some gear dependency with spells, and pure melees being the most gear dependent and hence loot centered.<br>
<br>
Making everyone dependent on gear to the extent that melees are would have the effect of making everyone necessarily into a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;loot whore,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and drive other player styles from the game.<br>
