<br>
On the subject of &quot;Are casters dependent on loot&quot;, I would say &quot;Yes&quot;. Once again it's not as drastic a difference as loot on a melee, but a difference nevertheless. A wizard is purely limited by his mana. An uber wizard with 4k+ mana, epic, manna robe, Greater Familiar, horse, 15FT items, lvl 60 Luclin spells etc etc is going to perform a HELL lot better than a wizard without. Necromancers generally seek to improve mana and hp...and thus a Necromancer with high hp regen (gained from a combination of items) and large manapool is definitely going to outperform a Necromancer without. The example of loot that you're bringing up is only focus items...but there already exist some excellent caster loot that benefits us without being imbued with a focus effect. However, there isn't enough of such loot, relative to melee loot.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Why can't this be accomplished simply by the introduction of more compelling caster loot, especially at the high end, without weakening spells and making casters dependent on gear? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Here is where I believe you're misunderstanding. For one thing, no class is *dependent* on gear (allow me to further elaborate). A lvl 60 Monk wearing &quot;common&quot; loot can still adequately perform his function. However, the same monk wearing uber loot may accomplish it better. And also, what you have said is exactly what everyone is asking. Focus items are only a portion of what could possibly be the balance that melees and casters needed, and even that is not yet set in stone. You have suggested the possible outcome that casters may have to switch out slots in order to accommodate. But that is already happened right now, to a lesser degree. You see casters switching out some of their slots for FT items. But that is not a big issue, simply because many items featuring a FT agent also has excellent primary stats. I see more or less the same thing happening with introducing items with focus effects.<br>
<br>
The problem of melee/caster balancing ultimately lies at the end game - where a caster simply cannot advance himself much more than what he already has, while there's still room for melees to improve. And while not neglecting the lower levels, the endgame is where Verant should be focusing mostly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showPrevMessage?topicID=175.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showNextMessage?topicID=175.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=175.topic&index=18><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.threadControl?topicID=175.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=175.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=175.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicia